Subject: [PATCH] net: stmmac: dwmac-tegra: fixed stream id for passthrough guests

A vfio-platform passthrough guest has no IOMMU, so
tegra_dev_iommu_get_stream_id() cannot supply MGBE0's SMMU stream id and the
driver bails with -EINVAL. Fall back to MGBE0's fixed stream id (6), which is
the value the MAC's ASID register must carry and what the driver hardcoded
before commit 426046e2d ("net: stmmac: dwmac-tegra: Read iommu stream id from
device tree"). This is applied only to the Net-VM guest kernel; the host keeps
the stock driver.

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/dwmac-tegra.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/dwmac-tegra.c
@@ -244,11 +244,14 @@
 	if (IS_ERR(mgbe->xpcs))
 		return PTR_ERR(mgbe->xpcs);
 
-	/* get controller's stream id from iommu property in device tree */
-	if (!tegra_dev_iommu_get_stream_id(mgbe->dev, &mgbe->iommu_sid)) {
-		dev_err(mgbe->dev, "failed to get iommu stream id\n");
-		return -EINVAL;
-	}
+	/*
+	 * Get the controller's stream id from the iommu property in the device
+	 * tree. A vfio-platform passthrough guest has no IOMMU, so fall back to
+	 * MGBE0's fixed stream id (6) -- the value the MAC's ASID register must
+	 * carry and what the driver hardcoded before commit 426046e2d.
+	 */
+	if (!tegra_dev_iommu_get_stream_id(mgbe->dev, &mgbe->iommu_sid))
+		mgbe->iommu_sid = 6;
 
 	res.addr = mgbe->regs;
 	res.irq = irq;
